posts.name: Tinnittin
posts.cooked: There is probably some error occurring when the robot code is starting. Can you share the logs and the code you are trying to deploy?
The deployed code is the SysId code, it’s not modified by the user.
Yes we are trying to use sysid and is not our code.

posts.name: Tinnittin
posts.cooked:
It looks to me that the code is deploying (hence the green “Deploy Complete!” on the dashboard), and the reason you are seeing “No Robot Code” is that the code is crashing. This could happen because:

the robot is trying to connect to a different gyro than what you are using,

the gyro you are using is in a different port,

or some other reason.

I’m asking for the logs to see if there are any error messages to confirm my suspicions or rule them out.

Not too sure what logs you’re looking for, I am posting all that I see. Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 227 KB

Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 227 KB

Screenshot (3) 1920×1080 227 KB

Untitled 1034×1085 301 KB

Untitled 1034×1085 301 KB

Untitled 1034×1085 301 KB

We confirmed the gyro is actually connected and working by running our own robot code and utilizing/printing out the gyro values. Confirmed port is the same as well.

Completely lost on what might be wrong… We can run it without the gyro but we also get a different error when using the analyzer with just the standard Encoders: “Acceleration filtering has removed all data… Please verify that your units and data is reasonable and then adjust your motion threshold, test duration, and/or window size to try to fix this issue.”
Noticed that you can pick any other Gyro and the robot code turns green.
